4. The Dual Ledger Requirement

The Delta Engine must maintain two ledgers.

A. Hit Ledger

Records:
	•	successful predictions
	•	partial successes
	•	convergence events
	•	repeated pattern confirmations

Fields:
	•	prediction
	•	observed match
	•	conditions present
	•	confidence before
	•	confidence after
	•	suspected invariant

⸻

B. Miss Ledger

Records:
	•	failed predictions
	•	false positives
	•	overextended interpretations
	•	timing failures
	•	mechanism failures

Fields:
	•	prediction
	•	actual outcome
	•	point of failure
	•	broken assumption
	•	revised boundary condition
	•	lesson extracted

⸻

5. Why Dual Ledgers Matter

A hit tells you:

“There may be signal here.”

A miss tells you:

“Here is where the signal stops.”

Without the Miss Ledger, the engine becomes:
	•	self-flattering
	•	confidence-distorting
	•	narrative-addicted
	•	increasingly untestable

With both ledgers, it becomes:
	•	sharpened
	•	bounded
	•	reusable
	•	auditable

