11. Operating Modes

Scout Mode

Loose exploration.
Used when mapping emerging patterns with low commitment.

Forge Mode

Hard testing.
Used when trying to break a promising pattern.

Ledger Mode

Archival and comparison.
Used to collect hits, misses, and revisions over time.

Doctrine Mode

Promotion and reuse.
Used only for patterns that survive repeated friction.

